    public interface GraphInterface<V,E>
    The root interface in the graph hierarchy. A mathematical graph-theory graph object G(V,E) contains a set V of vertices and a set E of edges. Each edge e=(v1,v2) in E connects vertex v1 to vertex v2. Through generics, a graph can be typed to specific classes for vertices V and edges E. Such a graph can contain vertices of type V and all sub-types and Edges of type E and all sub-types.
